# Product Overview

## What It Does
A PDF document search service. Users upload PDFs, the system extracts text via OCR, embeds it into vectors, and stores them in PostgreSQL+pgvector. Users can then search documents with natural language via web UI, REST API, or CLI chatbot.

## Three Interfaces

### Web UI (`templates/`, `app/main.py`)
- **Search Page** (`/`) — Query box with HTMX, displays matched chunks with document info and scores
- **Chat Page** (`/chat`) — Interactive chat interface with tool calling (replicates CLI chatbot)
- **Documents Page** (`/documents`) — List all uploaded documents with enrichment status
- **Document Detail** (`/documents/{id}`) — Document info, chunks, memories; supports reprocess
- Server-side rendered with Jinja2 templates, single-process architecture

### REST API (`app/routes.py`)
- `POST /api/v1/documents/upload` — Upload and process a single PDF
- `POST /api/v1/documents/query` — Semantic search + LLM-generated answer
- `POST /api/v1/documents/search` — Search-only endpoint (returns chunks, no LLM answer)
- `POST /api/v1/chat` — Chat endpoint with tool calling support
- `POST /api/v1/chat/tool` — Execute a single tool call (for chat UI)
- `GET /api/v1/documents` — List all documents
- `POST /api/v1/documents/{id}/reprocess` — Reprocess an errored batch-ingested document
- Endpoints detect HTMX requests and return HTML fragments when appropriate

### CLI Chatbot (`app/cli/chat.py`)
- Interactive REPL with conversation history
- LLM uses OpenAI tool calling to decide when to search
- Two tools: `search(query)` across all docs, `search_in_book(book_name, query)` for a specific doc
- System prompt includes the full document list with page counts

## Data Flow
1. **Ingest:** PDF → pdf2image → PP-Structure (layout+OCR+table) → blocks → chunks (1:1 text/table) → embeddings → pgvector
2. **Enrich** (optional): Chunks → LLM extracts context/fact memories → document metadata (title, description, tags)
3. **Search:** Query → (optional) LLM query expansion → vector search + enrichment boosts → Cohere rerank → results
4. **Answer:** Top chunks → LLM generates answer

## Ingestion Paths
- **Batch ingest** (`app/cli/ingest.py`): PDFs from `example-pdfs/`, uses `path` as unique key, cache in `cache/{doc_id}/`. Service: `app/services/ingest.py` (single-doc `ingest_pdf`).
- **Upload** (`routes.py`): Single PDF via API, in-memory processing, no path/cache (ephemeral)
- **Enrich** (`app/cli/enricher.py`): `make enrich` after ingest — populates `document_enrichments` and `memories`. Service: `app/services/enricher.py` (single-doc `enrich_document`).

## Search Evaluation
- **Test questions** (`app/cli/generate_test_questions.py`): Samples chunks+memories, uses LLM to generate one query per sampled chunk (direct, paraphrase, keyword, conceptual, etc.), stores in `search_test_questions`
- **Eval run** (`app/cli/run_search_eval.py`): Runs questions through `enhanced_search`, records chunk/doc ranks in `search_eval_results`, reports hit@1/2/4/8 and recall by query type
- Tables: `search_test_questions`, `search_eval_runs`, `search_eval_results`
- Commands: `make generate-questions N_QUESTIONS=30` (or `make test-questions`), `make search-eval`

## Project Structure
```
app/
├── main.py            # FastAPI app, lifespan, template routes
├── config.py          # pydantic-settings
├── database.py        # unified engines (async + sync), init_db, dispose_all
├── models.py          # Document, Chunk, DocumentEnrichment, Memory
├── schemas.py         # Pydantic request/response models
├── routes.py          # API endpoints (handles HTMX)
├── services/          # Business logic (single-doc primitives)
│   ├── search.py     # enhanced_search — multi-signal retrieval, enrichment boosts
│   ├── embeddings.py # OpenAI embeddings, Cohere rerank, LLM
│   ├── pdf_processing.py  # pdf2image, OCR, chunking
│   ├── ingest.py     # ingest_pdf — single-doc (API + CLI)
│   └── enricher.py   # enrich_document — single-doc
├── utils/
│   └── cache.py      # Disk cache for images/OCR (batch ingest only)
└── cli/              # Batch CLI entry points
    ├── ingest.py     # ingest, reingest, prune
    ├── enricher.py   # enrich, reenrich
    ├── chat.py       # Interactive chatbot
    ├── generate_test_questions.py  # Search eval: generate test questions
    └── run_search_eval.py  # Search eval: run eval, compute metrics
templates/
├── base.html              # Base template with navigation
├── search.html            # Search page
├── search_results.html    # Search results fragment (HTMX)
├── chat.html              # Chat page
├── documents.html         # Documents list
├── document_detail.html   # Document detail and chunks
└── document_card_fragment.html  # Document card (HTMX, reprocess)
static/
└── style.css          # Global stylesheet
```
